  <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 1rem;">
    <h1 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); color: #1A2E1A; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Editorial Standards</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; color: #4a5a4a; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">FishSmithLake.com is an independent fishing resource. We are not affiliated with Alabama Power, the Alabama Department of Conservation and Natural Resources, any government agency, or any fishing tackle brand. Our only obligation is to Smith Lake anglers.</p>

    <div style="line-height: 1.8; color: #334155;">

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: #2D6A4F; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;">Who We Are</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">FishSmithLake.com was built by people who fish Smith Lake and care about giving anglers accurate, useful information. We work with local experts, long-time residents, and verified data sources to make sure what we publish reflects the reality of fishing on this specific lake — not generic fishing advice repackaged with Smith Lake's name on it.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: #2D6A4F; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;">How We Research Content</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Every page on FishSmithLake.com is researched from at least one of the following sources:</p>
      <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Direct local knowledge</strong> — information from anglers, guides, and residents with documented experience on Lewis Smith Lake</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Government data</strong> — USGS water level data (Station 02450250), Alabama DCNR fishing regulations (outdooralabama.com), U.S. Forest Service recreation information</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Alabama Power records</strong> — shoreline management, lake elevation targets, dam operations data</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Published fisheries research</strong> — Alabama Department of Conservation and Natural Resources fish population surveys and stocking records</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">We do not publish generic fishing advice and label it as Smith Lake-specific. If we don't know something with confidence, we say so and direct readers to authoritative sources.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: #2D6A4F; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;">Data Sources by Topic</h2>
      <div style="overflow-x: auto; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          <thead>
            <tr style="background: #F0F7F0; border-bottom: 2px solid #D8E8D8;">
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem; color: #1A2E1A; font-weight: 600;">Topic</th>
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem; color: #1A2E1A; font-weight: 600;">Primary Source</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #D8E8D8;">
              <td style="padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;">Water levels</td>
              <td style="padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;">USGS Station 02450250</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #D8E8D8; background: #fafffe;">
              <td style="padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;">Fishing regulations</td>
              <td style="padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;">Alabama DCNR — outdooralabama.com</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #D8E8D8;">
              <td style="padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;">Shoreline &amp; dock permits</td>
              <td style="padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;">Alabama Power — apcshorelines.com</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #D8E8D8; background: #fafffe;">
              <td style="padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;">Lake geography &amp; depth</td>
              <td style="padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;">Alabama Power / USACE records</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #D8E8D8;">
              <td style="padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;">Species information</td>
              <td style="padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;">Alabama DCNR fisheries data</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background: #fafffe;">
              <td style="padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;">News</td>
              <td style="padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;">Google News RSS — Lewis Smith Lake and Alabama fishing queries</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: #2D6A4F; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;">Corrections Policy</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">We welcome corrections. If something on this site is wrong, outdated, or missing important local context, please use our contact form. We review and update content based on verified corrections from locals who know the lake.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: #2D6A4F; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;">Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">FishSmithLake.com participates in the Amazon Associates affiliate program. Some links on gear and lure recommendation pages are affiliate links — if you purchase through them, we earn a small commission at no additional cost to you. This does not influence our recommendations. We only recommend gear we believe is genuinely effective for Smith Lake fishing.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: #2D6A4F; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;">Real Estate Disclaimer</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">Justin Dyar (<a href="https://justindyar.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color: #2D6A4F;">justindyar.com</a>) is referenced on this site as a local Smith Lake waterfront real estate expert. This is an editorial reference based on his documented experience and local reputation — not a paid advertisement. FishSmithLake.com does not receive compensation for referring readers to justindyar.com.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: #2D6A4F; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;">Contact</h2>
      <p>Corrections, tips, and local knowledge contributions: <a href="/contact" style="color: #2D6A4F;">fishsmithlake.com/contact</a></p>

    </div>
  </div>
